node.text: I am so grateful for my country where I get to watch my children play on the sand without a care in the world (other than “can I have one more s’more?”), where I can speak about my faith with confidence and without fear of someone stopping me, and where I’m able to go sleep at night in peace knowing I live in a country that fights for our freedom. Grateful for the men and women and families who have sacrificed it all for our freedoms today ❤️🤍💙 Happy Memorial Day (yesterday & everyday🥰) & God Bless America 🇺🇸🇺🇸

node.text: missing our mamas weekend girls trip already 🥰 i wish we could go back and do it all again (minus all the sick pregnant moments 🤢💗). so many laughs, lots of ice cream🍦, Kenny, sunshine ☀️☀️☀️, bike rides (Dee never wrecked🎉), the 2 pregnant girls changed a tire (swipe to see our super tough pic 💪🏽💪🏽), dolphins every day playing in the water 💙🐬, beautiful sunsets 💛🧡❤️, when 6 umbrellas blew into the ocean we executed an umbrella rescue mission⛱ (then I realized I’m out of cardio shape, pregnant & I haven’t done that much exercise in a solid 10 weeks at least, for some reason I chose to rescue the furthest away umbrella, got REALLY far past the second sand bar-the umbrella was moving FAST-and asked my new bestie Hannah Grace from Clemson to help bring me in on her paddle board because I was STRUGGLING 🤪 thank you Hannah Grace 🤍) and the most giant stingray the size of Moana’s grandmother swam right under me😍, read GOOD books, took naps, got minor sunburns, then met the boys in TX for TR’s shows 💛 y’all ready to go back?? Love you girls so much 😘😘😘💕
